FINDING 1: [SEVERITY: HIGH]
Category: Security
Description: reconcileOrphanedContainers filters containers solely on `agentpaas.resource-type=agent` (no `agentpaas.managed-by=agentpaas` check). Any user or malicious container can set this label and be selected for stop+remove.
Location: internal/daemon/control_handlers.go:1040
Impact: Attacker can cause deletion of arbitrary containers (or their own to DoS) by crafting labels; label is not trustworthy/owned-only.
Fix: Add managed-by filter (or post-filter with IsOwned) to ListContainers call, matching the pattern used in reconcile.go and network handling.

FINDING 2: [SEVERITY: MEDIUM]
Category: Security
Description: No check that listed containers are actually owned before Remove; relies only on label filter.
Location: internal/daemon/control_handlers.go:1044-1057
Impact: Same as #1 — label spoofing leads to unauthorized container destruction.
Fix: After listing, filter results using runtime.IsOwned(c.Labels) before acting.

FINDING 3: [SEVERITY: LOW]
Category: Security
Description: Containers are removed even if Stop fails (Remove always attempted on line 1054 regardless of prior Stop error).
Location: internal/daemon/control_handlers.go:1050-1054
Impact: Minor — force-remove proceeds, but error path is silent; no guarantee of clean stop.
Fix: Log but continue (current behavior is acceptable for orphans).

FINDING 4: [SEVERITY: MEDIUM]
Category: Race Conditions
Description: knownRuns snapshot taken under runMu then lock released before ListContainers + removal loop. gRPC server is registered (line 302) and listening before reconcile; Run handler can call trackRun concurrently.
Location: internal/daemon/control_handlers.go:1031-1036,1044; internal/daemon/server.go:302-306
Impact: TOCTOU race: a Run RPC arriving during reconciliation can have its newly-tracked container removed as orphan.
Fix: Keep lock held during the entire operation, or use a generation/epoch token, or perform reconcile before registering the gRPC server.

FINDING 5: [SEVERITY: MEDIUM]
Category: Race Conditions
Description: reconcile runs before d.started=true and before Ready(), but readinessInterceptor only gates after started/ready; concurrent RPCs possible in the narrow window.
Location: internal/daemon/server.go:304-308
Impact: Race window for new runs to be orphaned immediately.
Fix: Move reconcile after Ready() or ensure it is atomic with server readiness.

FINDING 6: [SEVERITY: LOW]
Category: Resource Leaks
Description: ListNetworks (internal filter) is called inside the per-container orphan loop (line 1060), causing repeated identical calls.
Location: internal/daemon/control_handlers.go:1060
Impact: Inefficiency (O(n) redundant Docker calls) when many orphans; no correctness leak but wasteful.
Fix: List networks once outside the container loop.

FINDING 7: [SEVERITY: MEDIUM]
Category: Resource Leaks
Description: If rt.Remove fails (line 1054), continue skips the subsequent network cleanup for that container's runID.
Location: internal/daemon/control_handlers.go:1056
Impact: Orphaned internal network for that runID is never cleaned up in this pass (second network pass only catches managed-by nets without runID match in knownRuns).
Fix: Separate container removal from network cleanup or ensure network removal is attempted even on container remove failure.

